incident_updates.body: We have determined the origin of the incident affecting our Dedicated Servers offer on the specific rack. Here are some supplementary details : Start time : 23/04/2025 16:16 UTC Impacted Service(s) : Servers in rack LIM0309B05C are temporarily unavailable. Customers Impact : Customers are temporarily unable to access and use their servers in rack LIM0309B05C. Root Cause : This incident is caused by an electrical equipment issue. Ongoing Actions : The incident has been identified and our teams are mobilized to restore service as quickly as possible. We will keep you updated on the progress and resolution. We apologize for any inconvenience caused and appreciate your understanding.

We are currently experiencing an incident affecting our Dedicated Servers offering, which is causing temporary Availability issues in the specified rack. Here is detail for this incident : Start time : 23/04/2025 16:16 UTC Impacted Service(s) : Servers in rack LIM0309B05C are temporarily unavailable. Customers Impact : Customers are temporarily unable to access and use their servers in rack LIM0309B05C. Ongoing Actions : Our teams are investigating to determine the origin of the incident to fix it. We will keep you updated on the progress and resolution. We apologize for any inconvenience caused and appreciate your understanding.

Service improvement : As part of our continuous improvement policy, we will be doing a maintenance on a network equipment. Thank you for your understanding.

scheduled_maintenances.name: [GLOBAL][Baremetal] - Debian-10-based rescue system (rescue-customer boot mode) removal

incident_updates.body: As part of our continuous improvement plan, maintenance is scheduled on our Baremetal offer. Start time : 23/06/2025 09:00 UTC End time : 23/06/2025 13:00 UTC Service impact : The Debian-10-based rescue system (rescue-customer boot mode) will no longer be available after 23/06/2025. Service improvement : The objective of this maintenance is to remove the Debian-10-based rescue system (rescue-customer boot mode) for all Baremetal products. Customers should start using the new Debian-12-based rescue system (rescue12-customer). Thank you for your understanding.
